01:13:05.464 --> 01:13:07.882
I think more,
the women came at him.

01:13:08.050 --> 01:13:10.802
- ♪ That why they say ♪
- ♪ Nice one... ♪

01:13:10.969 --> 01:13:12.804
- Interviewer: Was he faithful?
- Diane Jobson: To whom? God?

01:13:12.971 --> 01:13:15.306
To Jah? Yes, he was
faithful to Jah.

01:13:15.474 --> 01:13:18.393
Faithful to any one woman? No.

01:13:18.560 --> 01:13:20.561
Why? Somebody own him?

01:13:22.398 --> 01:13:24.774
What is fidelity?
Western ideology, you know.

01:13:24.942 --> 01:13:27.318
A ring on your finger,
a ring through your nose?

01:13:27.486 --> 01:13:30.029
That's for Western men, man.

01:13:30.197 --> 01:13:31.739
They can only handle
one woman at a time.

01:13:31.907 --> 01:13:33.991
Bob could handle more.

01:13:35.661 --> 01:13:37.954
♪ Kinky reggae now... ♪

01:13:38.122 --> 01:13:41.165
Williams: One day, a lady
came to me and she said,

01:13:41.333 --> 01:13:45.336
"Didn't anyone tell you that Bob
was married?" And l didn't know.

01:13:45.504 --> 01:13:48.464
For a time there l never knew
that he was legally married.

01:13:48.632 --> 01:13:52.760
I did come to know.
Eventually, his mom told me.

01:13:52.928 --> 01:13:54.846
Interviewer:
Did he see Rita at all at that time?

01:13:55.013 --> 01:13:57.557
Sure. I mean,
they worked together, you know.

01:13:57.724 --> 01:13:59.350
Toured the world together.

01:14:00.602 --> 01:14:03.855
When we were on tour,
Rita had her own room.

01:14:04.022 --> 01:14:06.023
She was not with Bob.

01:14:06.191 --> 01:14:09.193
She would see everything
that goes on,

01:14:09.361 --> 01:14:13.197
but she had maximum respect
for the work.

01:14:15.868 --> 01:14:17.410
Interviewer: How did you cope
through all the years

01:14:17.578 --> 01:14:19.829
that you were married together,
and Bob was having

01:14:19.997 --> 01:14:22.123
these relationships
with other women?

01:14:22.291 --> 01:14:25.084
( Chuckles )
l became his... his guardian angel.

01:14:25.252 --> 01:14:27.503
( Iaughing )
And then by that time,

01:14:27.671 --> 01:14:31.716
l was past the surface
of being just a wife,

01:14:31.884 --> 01:14:36.888
because of the importance
of who l knew Bob is.

01:14:37.055 --> 01:14:40.308
I didn't see it as a fun trip.
We were on a mission.

01:14:40.476 --> 01:14:43.227
It was like
an evangelist campaign

01:14:43.395 --> 01:14:45.480
to bring people closer to Jah.

01:14:47.274 --> 01:14:50.985
Cedella: They had this...
this bond, you know?

01:14:51.153 --> 01:14:52.403
I wouldn't.

01:14:52.571 --> 01:14:54.489
I mean, you know,

01:14:54.656 --> 01:14:56.407
if that was my husband,
l wouldn't.

01:14:58.577 --> 01:15:02.747
Rita: We never fought about women.
We would never get into that.

01:15:02.915 --> 01:15:04.373
He would come and say to me,

01:15:04.541 --> 01:15:08.711
"Rita, I did this,"
or "This is what happened."

01:15:08.879 --> 01:15:11.881
l was the one that he would call to get
women out of his dressing room

01:15:12.049 --> 01:15:13.799
when it get to that stage.

01:15:13.967 --> 01:15:17.553
"Come up for my room.
Come and get these people out for me."

01:15:17.721 --> 01:15:19.138
And l would do that gracefully.

01:15:19.306 --> 01:15:21.349
"Come on, ladies. It's bedtime.

01:15:21.517 --> 01:15:23.684
We have a show tomorrow, so..."

01:15:24.728 --> 01:15:27.021
She wouldn't get upset,
you know,

01:15:27.189 --> 01:15:32.068
but... there were times
when, you know,

01:15:32.236 --> 01:15:34.111
you knew she was hurting.

01:15:35.113 --> 01:15:37.448
It hurt all of us.

01:15:37.616 --> 01:15:40.409
And that's what he didn't like.

01:15:40.577 --> 01:15:43.454
He didn't like it when, like,
we knew that she was hurt

01:15:43.622 --> 01:15:45.706
and it showed on us.

01:15:45.874 --> 01:15:47.708
That's when, "Okay,
we're going for ice cream."

01:15:47.876 --> 01:15:50.294
We're going for burgers.
What do you want?"

01:15:50.462 --> 01:15:53.214
lnterviewer: Do you think that
he was being selfish?

01:15:53.382 --> 01:15:56.384
Yes. It's not fair to no woman.

01:15:57.678 --> 01:15:59.387
That is not fair at all,

01:15:59.555 --> 01:16:02.640
but we still couldn't
hate him for it.

01:16:04.268 --> 01:16:06.811
( Song ends )

01:16:06.979 --> 01:16:08.980
( audience applauding,
cheering )

01:16:20.325 --> 01:16:21.659
Reporter:
In the capital of Kingston,

01:16:21.827 --> 01:16:24.161
there are rival
shantytown ghettos

01:16:24.329 --> 01:16:25.663
where whole communities
are divided

01:16:25.831 --> 01:16:27.832
along sectarian lines.

01:16:28.000 --> 01:16:29.458
These zones are controlled

01:16:29.626 --> 01:16:32.128
by the prime minister's
People's National Party,

01:16:32.296 --> 01:16:34.422
who are accused
of being communists,

01:16:34.590 --> 01:16:36.674
or by the opposition,
Jamaica Labour Party,

01:16:36.842 --> 01:16:38.926
who are accused
of being fascists.

01:16:40.053 --> 01:16:42.680
Politics in Jamaica
at that time

01:16:42.848 --> 01:16:46.058
was like an East-West
confrontation,

01:16:46.226 --> 01:16:47.685
which was scary.

01:16:47.853 --> 01:16:49.812
You have one side
which is kind of

01:16:49.980 --> 01:16:52.857
more ultraconservative,
right-wing,

01:16:53.025 --> 01:16:54.567
which is Seaga,

01:16:54.735 --> 01:16:57.361
who was like Reagan's man
in the Caribbean.

01:16:57.529 --> 01:17:00.865
And then Manley was trying
to work a system

01:17:01.033 --> 01:17:03.451
called democratic socialism,

01:17:03.619 --> 01:17:05.536
which other parties say,

01:17:05.704 --> 01:17:08.372
"That's just a disguise for
saying you're a communist."

01:17:08.540 --> 01:17:11.626
Reporter: Sometimes it's only insults
or stones and bottles

01:17:11.793 --> 01:17:13.586
thrown from one side
to the other,

01:17:13.754 --> 01:17:15.588
but often it's bombs
and bullets,

01:17:15.756 --> 01:17:18.924
and almost every day
the newspapers carry fresh reports

01:17:19.092 --> 01:17:21.052
of the previous day's
killings in Kingston.

01:17:22.596 --> 01:17:25.723
Rita: The whole thing became
like a gangster thing.

01:17:25.891 --> 01:17:27.725
Political gangster.

01:17:27.893 --> 01:17:30.686
These were the guys
who kept things in line

01:17:30.854 --> 01:17:32.938
for the MPs, you know.

01:17:33.106 --> 01:17:35.274
So you find that in some areas,

01:17:35.442 --> 01:17:38.653
the real power is enforcers.

01:17:38.820 --> 01:17:41.447
You like this girl...
that's both of us.

01:17:41.615 --> 01:17:44.033
You like her and l like her.
We start a fight over her.

01:17:44.201 --> 01:17:45.409
It's just that.

01:17:45.577 --> 01:17:48.746
Him like PNP. You like JLP.

01:17:48.914 --> 01:17:50.706
You wanna fight for your PNP.

01:17:52.417 --> 01:17:54.835
Bob was friends
with all of those guys.

01:17:55.003 --> 01:17:58.339
AII of the bad guys from
the Labour Party was Bob friend.

01:17:58.507 --> 01:18:01.967
Likewise, all the bad guys
from the PNP.

01:18:03.220 --> 01:18:04.762
Smith: These are guys
that come from

01:18:04.930 --> 01:18:07.098
the same neighborhood
he grew up with.

01:18:07.265 --> 01:18:09.809
These are really bad guys.
( Iaughing )

01:18:09.976 --> 01:18:11.310
'Cause you might
see some guys, yeah,

01:18:11.478 --> 01:18:15.523
and then tomorrow you'd
take up the Jamaican paper,

01:18:15.691 --> 01:18:17.441
you'd see
the 10-most-wanted list...

01:18:17.609 --> 01:18:20.277
four of the guys
that were on it were dead.

01:18:20.445 --> 01:18:22.071
There are now five.
( laughing )

01:18:23.448 --> 01:18:25.449
Some of them actually
love the music, you know,

01:18:25.617 --> 01:18:28.452
but their main thing is, you know...
( laughing )

01:18:28.620 --> 01:18:31.122
warfare and badness, you know.

01:18:32.332 --> 01:18:34.458
( Bob speaking )

01:18:47.764 --> 01:18:50.307
Bob did a concert

01:18:50.475 --> 01:18:53.853
with Stevie Wonder in Jamaica,

01:18:54.020 --> 01:18:57.940
and they actually performed
two songs together.

01:18:58.108 --> 01:19:00.818
I think "Very Superstitious,"
which Bob knew,

01:19:00.986 --> 01:19:03.320
and "l Shot the Sheriff."

01:19:04.823 --> 01:19:07.616
♪ l shot the sheriff ♪

01:19:08.994 --> 01:19:13.122
♪ But l did not shoot
the deputy... ♪

01:19:14.875 --> 01:19:17.501
Garrick: Stevie made a gesture
by giving, I think,

01:19:17.669 --> 01:19:19.670
half of his pay for the show

01:19:19.838 --> 01:19:23.132
to the Salvation Army
blind school in Jamaica,

01:19:23.300 --> 01:19:26.677
and l think Bob
was moved by that.

01:19:26.845 --> 01:19:31.515
And Bob said, "Well,
we'll give a free concert."

01:19:31.683 --> 01:19:35.144
They took that idea
to Michael Manley,

01:19:35.312 --> 01:19:38.063
who was just down the road...
the prime minister...

01:19:38.231 --> 01:19:42.026
and they were, like,
enthused about it.

01:19:42.194 --> 01:19:45.029
Reporter: Bob Marley, the world's
leading exponent of reggae music,

01:19:45.197 --> 01:19:47.323
has agreed to appear
in a major free concert

01:19:47.491 --> 01:19:49.825
to be held for the benefit
of the Jamaican people

01:19:49.993 --> 01:19:51.869
in Kingston on Sunday,
December 5th.

01:19:52.037 --> 01:19:55.456
The announcement was made at a press
conference held at Jamaica House

01:19:55.624 --> 01:19:57.541
by Marley,
his manager Don Taylor,

01:19:57.709 --> 01:19:59.335
and the parliamentary
secretary in charge

01:19:59.503 --> 01:20:01.545
of cultural information,
Arnold Bertram.

01:20:01.713 --> 01:20:04.048
Blackwell: Well, l think he got
tricked into it,

01:20:04.216 --> 01:20:06.759
'cause he rang me and asked me
if l thought he should do the concert.

01:20:06.927 --> 01:20:08.928
And l said, "Well,
if it's the prime minister",

01:20:09.095 --> 01:20:11.555
then you're doing it
for the country.

01:20:11.723 --> 01:20:13.766
But if there's going to be
an election soon,

01:20:13.934 --> 01:20:17.061
"then you're doing it for him
rather than the country."

01:20:17.229 --> 01:20:20.689
Reporter: Two weeks following that
announcement on November 22nd,

01:20:20.857 --> 01:20:22.733
Jamaica's prime minister,
Michael Manley,

01:20:22.901 --> 01:20:26.070
called new general elections
for December 15th.

01:20:26.238 --> 01:20:29.824
Garrick: lf we knew that election
was going to happen

01:20:29.991 --> 01:20:32.743
in that space of time,
we'd have never done that concert.

01:20:33.745 --> 01:20:35.746
( Bob speaking )

01:20:38.834 --> 01:20:40.417
Interviewer:
So with the upcoming election,

01:20:40.585 --> 01:20:44.380
you don't really want to think about
or care who wins?

01:20:44.548 --> 01:20:45.923
( Bob speaking )

01:20:49.886 --> 01:20:52.263
Remember, Bob is becoming
very popular,

01:20:52.430 --> 01:20:55.057
and whoever side
Bob seems to be on,

01:20:55.225 --> 01:20:56.934
that's the side
people gonna be on.

01:20:57.102 --> 01:21:00.604
Hell, Bob had a lot of control
down there in Jamaica, man.

01:21:00.772 --> 01:21:03.274
And them politicians
didn't like that.

01:21:03.441 --> 01:21:05.943
Bob, I think,
had overexposed himself

01:21:06.111 --> 01:21:07.945
on the political side,

01:21:08.113 --> 01:21:11.657
and that was bound to draw
the anger of some others

01:21:11.825 --> 01:21:13.450
because he had friends
on both sides.

01:21:13.618 --> 01:21:16.620
The thing was, like,
you have to be on one side.

01:21:16.788 --> 01:21:18.455
You have to be on some side.

01:21:18.623 --> 01:21:21.834
You can't be in the middle,
or you can get hurt.

01:21:26.131 --> 01:21:28.924
Garrick: We'd feel a little
kind of tension,

01:21:29.092 --> 01:21:32.845
but, you know, the politics
kind of getting hot.

01:21:33.013 --> 01:21:35.639
Mowatt: There were people saying
that they heard

01:21:35.807 --> 01:21:39.310
that they were gonna
shoot up the concert.

01:21:39.477 --> 01:21:40.978
Kinsey:
People in the group, you know,

01:21:41.146 --> 01:21:44.315
the musicians
and The l-Threes...

01:21:44.482 --> 01:21:48.485
every day, as it would
get closer to this day of the concert,

01:21:48.653 --> 01:21:52.823
people was feeling hesitant
about doing it.

01:21:52.991 --> 01:21:55.367
They had a fear for it.

01:21:57.996 --> 01:22:01.248
Mowatt: Every night there would be
rehearsal at 56 Hope Road

01:22:01.416 --> 01:22:03.417
for the concert.

01:22:05.337 --> 01:22:07.588
Garrick:
We usually had two guys

01:22:07.756 --> 01:22:10.299
from equivalent
to the Secret Service.

01:22:10.467 --> 01:22:12.301
They call them
the Protective Service.

01:22:12.469 --> 01:22:15.512
They, like, protect
the prime minister and stuff.

01:22:15.680 --> 01:22:17.848
And they used to
come every night,

01:22:18.016 --> 01:22:20.851
but they never came that night.

01:22:21.019 --> 01:22:24.855
We had took a break, so everybody
was kind of floating around.

01:22:25.023 --> 01:22:28.817
Don Taylor, Bob, and myself

01:22:28.985 --> 01:22:32.446
was in the kitchen.

01:22:32.614 --> 01:22:35.950
I was in the car, you know,
getting ready to come out.

01:22:36.117 --> 01:22:38.869
I see some men
going up the steps.

01:22:39.037 --> 01:22:43.666
The gunman approached
from the side here

01:22:43.833 --> 01:22:47.211
and kind of pushed his gun
through here.

01:22:47.379 --> 01:22:50.589
Well, you see a black glove
with a gun in it pointing up,

01:22:50.757 --> 01:22:53.759
you know... there was
nowhere else to go in the kitchen

01:22:53.927 --> 01:22:56.095
'cause we just,
like, at the wall.

01:22:57.806 --> 01:23:00.557
And then l heard the gunshots.

01:23:01.768 --> 01:23:04.061
( Gunshots )

01:23:08.024 --> 01:23:11.527
- Then they turned the gun on the car.
- ( Gunshots )

01:23:11.695 --> 01:23:14.321
l felt the warmest of blood
running down,

01:23:14.489 --> 01:23:16.573
and then l realized l was shot.

01:23:16.741 --> 01:23:18.742
The cat just
kept on shooting, man,

01:23:18.910 --> 01:23:20.577
till he ran out of bullets.

01:23:20.745 --> 01:23:22.246
The one hold a gun to my head,

01:23:22.414 --> 01:23:24.456
and one said to the other one,
"Everybody dead?"

01:23:24.624 --> 01:23:27.251
And the other said, "Yeah, man,
everybody dead. Everybody dead."

01:23:27.419 --> 01:23:29.378
Next thing l see Don Taylor
come out, man,

01:23:29.546 --> 01:23:32.423
and, like, blood pouring out of him
like ketchup, man.

01:23:32.590 --> 01:23:35.551
And then he finally
collapsed right there on the floor.

01:23:35.719 --> 01:23:37.052
I'm, like, "Man!"

01:23:37.220 --> 01:23:39.763
And I'm shouting out for Bob,
and then I heard a voice

01:23:39.931 --> 01:23:42.641
who I recognized
as Carly Barrett coming from...

01:23:42.809 --> 01:23:44.768
he said, "Bob is all right."

01:23:46.104 --> 01:23:47.604
Bob is all right."

01:23:49.691 --> 01:23:51.942
He had a burn right...

01:23:52.110 --> 01:23:54.570
the bullet traveled right here

01:23:54.738 --> 01:23:56.697
and actually lodged in his arm.

01:23:58.700 --> 01:24:00.492
Kinsey:
It's just a miracle, man,

01:24:00.660 --> 01:24:02.828
that nobody died
from that, man.

01:24:02.996 --> 01:24:05.205
Interviewer: So, it wasn't really
a professional hit?

01:24:05.373 --> 01:24:07.249
Well, as professional
as Jamaica is.

01:24:07.417 --> 01:24:10.169
They watch a lot of movies.
( chuckles )

01:24:10.336 --> 01:24:12.629
( siren wailing )

01:24:12.797 --> 01:24:15.466
Reporter: Here now is a special
item of news.

01:24:15.633 --> 01:24:18.552
Entertainer and reggae star,
Bob Marley,

01:24:18.720 --> 01:24:21.430
Rita Marley and the manager
of The Wailers, Don Taylor,

01:24:21.598 --> 01:24:24.099
are now patients
in the University Hospital

01:24:24.267 --> 01:24:25.809
after receiving gunshot wounds

01:24:25.977 --> 01:24:29.313
during a shooting
incident tonight.

01:24:34.944 --> 01:24:38.530
( Bob speaking )

01:24:49.000 --> 01:24:50.918
That's one thing for sure...

01:24:51.086 --> 01:24:54.296
that they was trying to stop
that concert from happening.

01:24:54.464 --> 01:24:56.131
The whole thing about
whether the concert

01:24:56.299 --> 01:24:58.133
was gonna happen or not...
there was so much pressure.

01:24:58.301 --> 01:25:00.427
There was pressure
from everywhere.

01:25:00.595 --> 01:25:02.846
I was just scared
Bob would get assassinated.

01:25:07.018 --> 01:25:08.852
Reporter:
In the twilight inside the arena,

01:25:09.020 --> 01:25:10.562
the crowd is fenced off

01:25:10.730 --> 01:25:12.147
and armed police are positioned

01:25:12.315 --> 01:25:14.233
all around the park.

01:25:14.400 --> 01:25:16.693
Five hours after the concert
was due to begin,

01:25:16.861 --> 01:25:20.364
the star, Bob Marley,
is still not there.

01:25:20.532 --> 01:25:23.283
Jobson: Some were trying to say,
"Bob, don't go.

01:25:23.451 --> 01:25:26.453
They didn't get you.
They may try for you again."

01:25:26.621 --> 01:25:29.957
Everyone saying, "You really
wanna do it, boss?"

01:25:30.125 --> 01:25:32.042
And him saying...
he said, "Yes."

01:25:32.210 --> 01:25:34.711
I said, "Hey, you know,
I'm with you, man."

01:25:34.879 --> 01:25:36.213
If you wanna do it,
let's do it."

01:25:36.381 --> 01:25:38.882
Mowatt: The police came for him
and took him down,

