02:02:57.286 --> 02:03:00.246
Eddie: The next day, we were out
in Central Park jogging.

02:03:00.414 --> 02:03:03.124
And we was going up this hill,

02:03:03.292 --> 02:03:06.920
and all of a sudden he...
he stumbled.

02:03:07.088 --> 02:03:10.632
And we went and we laid him down
on the side of the trail,

02:03:10.800 --> 02:03:12.467
and he... he started shaking,

02:03:12.635 --> 02:03:14.928
and he had foaming
at the mouth.

02:03:15.096 --> 02:03:18.473
And l said... when l looked at him,
he looked real strange.

02:03:18.641 --> 02:03:22.685
And the guys gathered around him,
they said something in patois.

02:03:22.853 --> 02:03:25.980
And he hollered "Rastafari"
and jumped up off the ground.

02:03:26.148 --> 02:03:29.109
Scared me to death. I mean, he was
there, shaking and foaming.

02:03:29.276 --> 02:03:31.486
Next thing l know, he done...
he just jumped up.

02:03:34.532 --> 02:03:37.659
Danny: We took him to the hospital
next door to my house.

02:03:39.036 --> 02:03:41.871
The doctor told Allan and me

02:03:42.039 --> 02:03:46.126
that Bob Marley had cancer
and that it had spread.

02:03:46.293 --> 02:03:49.671
He had cancer
all over his body...

02:03:49.839 --> 02:03:53.174
lungs, brain,
all over the place.

02:03:53.342 --> 02:03:56.845
It was incredible that he was able
to keep working.

02:03:58.472 --> 02:04:02.559
Danny: But the doctor told us
that we shouldn't do anything,

02:04:02.726 --> 02:04:06.187
that we should just let him
stay on the concert tour,

02:04:06.355 --> 02:04:08.523
that he was so strong
and powerful,

02:04:08.691 --> 02:04:12.694
that one day he was gonna walk out
onstage and he was gonna fall dead.

02:04:13.821 --> 02:04:16.364
But that he could not
be treated

02:04:16.532 --> 02:04:18.658
and he could not be helped.

02:04:20.077 --> 02:04:21.828
Interviewer:
How did he take the news?

02:04:21.996 --> 02:04:25.206
Bad. He took the news bad.

02:04:28.335 --> 02:04:30.795
Blackwell: l knew he'd had a problem
with his toe before that,

02:04:30.963 --> 02:04:35.592
but l had forgotten about it.

02:04:35.759 --> 02:04:38.011
I think everybody seemed
to have forgotten about it

02:04:38.179 --> 02:04:42.056
because if he'd been going
to regular checkups,

02:04:42.224 --> 02:04:46.769
you know, he might have been...
he might be around today. But...

02:04:46.937 --> 02:04:48.354
lnterviewer:
He just didn't go to his checkups?

02:04:48.522 --> 02:04:50.231
No.

02:04:58.616 --> 02:05:01.868
Mowatt:
The next stop was Pittsburgh,

02:05:02.036 --> 02:05:05.955
