to come on the bus

02:05:06.123 --> 02:05:08.625
for all of us
to drive to Pittsburgh.

02:05:08.792 --> 02:05:10.585
And we never saw Bob.

02:05:13.714 --> 02:05:15.924
Finally, he arrived,

02:05:16.091 --> 02:05:19.093
and he was looking
very, very stressed, l remember,

02:05:19.261 --> 02:05:22.597
and we went to do
a sound check.

02:05:22.765 --> 02:05:26.643
And I remember
we did the sound check

02:05:26.810 --> 02:05:28.728
with one song

02:05:28.896 --> 02:05:32.273
and we did that song
for maybe two or three hours.

02:05:32.441 --> 02:05:34.359
"I'm Hurting lnside."

02:05:36.320 --> 02:05:38.947
Mowatt: lt's the longest sound check
we have ever had.

02:05:39.114 --> 02:05:44.077
It just felt like, "Why?"
We didn't understand.

02:05:49.458 --> 02:05:52.043
We had a meeting before the show,
half an hour before the show,

02:05:52.211 --> 02:05:56.130
and we were told by Allan Cole
that this was gonna be our last concert.

02:05:57.466 --> 02:06:01.010
And, of course, we were all,
like, in shock.

02:06:01.178 --> 02:06:03.054
Cole: Before we went onstage,
he said to me,

02:06:03.222 --> 02:06:06.474
"l want you to stay pretty close in case
anything should happen."

02:06:06.642 --> 02:06:09.519
I'm saying, "Nothing's gonna happen to
you. Everything's gonna be all right."

02:06:09.687 --> 02:06:11.938
But he just said,
"Stay close in case."

02:06:12.106 --> 02:06:14.357
Just in case he got a seizure.

02:06:14.525 --> 02:06:18.987
♪ I wanna love you,
