uncomfortable,

02:07:51.914 --> 02:07:53.748
and he decided to cut it.

02:07:53.916 --> 02:07:55.792
That was quite a night.

02:07:58.420 --> 02:08:02.090
It was myself, Rita...
a group of us women.

02:08:02.257 --> 02:08:05.593
We lit candles, and we were reading
from the Bible.

02:08:05.761 --> 02:08:08.096
We were reading
the "Book of Job,"

02:08:08.263 --> 02:08:11.641
and we cut.

02:08:11.809 --> 02:08:14.268
I said to him...

02:08:16.313 --> 02:08:18.690
"You going for
the Rude Boy look?"

02:08:18.857 --> 02:08:20.858
And he laughed. It was funny.

02:08:21.026 --> 02:08:22.944
But it was really,
really sad...

02:08:23.112 --> 02:08:25.822
the saddest thing
l can ever remember.

02:08:28.158 --> 02:08:30.159
That was the first time
l saw him...

02:08:32.454 --> 02:08:34.539
like, without his hair.

02:08:34.707 --> 02:08:37.333
You know, he looked,
like, so tiny.

02:08:57.646 --> 02:09:00.982
Fraser: Him say, "Listen, we're
gonna fight it, all right?"

02:09:01.150 --> 02:09:04.485
Regardless of what the doctors might say
or what they might do,

02:09:04.653 --> 02:09:06.779
we're gonna fight it,

02:09:06.947 --> 02:09:08.823
"'cause a Rasta never give up."

02:09:08.991 --> 02:09:11.576
Left to me, l would have said,

02:09:11.744 --> 02:09:14.996
"Bob, come home to St. Ann and come eat
roast fish and callaloo every day."

02:09:15.164 --> 02:09:16.873
Smoke the biggest spliff
if you like,

02:09:17.040 --> 02:09:21.085
drink fish tea,
just do what you want.

02:09:21.253 --> 02:09:24.005
And if you end up in the same place
at the end of it all,

02:09:24.173 --> 02:09:28.050
at least you will
have had some comfort

02:09:28.218 --> 02:09:29.844
in your last months
on this earth

02:09:30.012 --> 02:09:33.181
"and being in a place that you really,
really wanted to be in."

02:09:33.348 --> 02:09:36.142
But we girls didn't have
